  node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/register-commands.spec.ts,null,project,240,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null
body: "## Repro (pm 2026.6.13 build)\n```\npm create feature --title 'x' --json   # => item.type == 'Task'  (BUG: positional 'feature' dropped)\npm create Feature 'x' --json           # => item.type == 'Feature' (positional title path OK)\npm create --type Feature --title 'x'   # => item.type == 'Feature' (explicit flag OK)\n```\nWhen a leading positional type name is given together with the `--title` flag, the positional type is ignored and create falls back to the default type (Task). Only the `<type> <title>` all-positional form or the explicit `--type` flag are honored.\n\n## Expected\nA leading positional that matches a known/registered type should set the item type regardless of whether the title arrives positionally or via `--title`. Otherwise emit a usage error rather than silently mistyping (agent footgun — see closed pm-edge for the create-type mistype class).\n\nDiscovered during the GH-210/GH-212 validate work (pm-gnnb) while seeding sandbox fixtures."
